</line><line>Apollo:
...B-But!
</line><line>Ga'ran:
<a href="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/aceattorney/images/5/57/SoJ_Such_insolence%21.png/revision/latest?cb=20220420132822" class="image"><img alt="SoJ Such insolence!" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="260" height="173" data-image-name="SoJ Such insolence!.png" data-image-key="SoJ_Such_insolence%21.png" data-relevant="1" data-src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/aceattorney/images/5/57/SoJ_Such_insolence%21.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/260?cb=20220420132822" class="lazyload" /></a>
</line><line>Ga'ran:
You have wasted more than enough of my time, lawyer. Do you not see the futility of your desparate floundering? The immutability of his duty? It is time to accept defeat.
</line><line>Apollo:
Arrrgh!
</line><line>Ga'ran:
Heh heh heh. Now, watch as the hammer of justice comes down upon your dear brother. Your Magistry. The verdict, if you will.
</line><line>Judge:
Y-Yes, Your Eminence!
</line><line>Apollo:
<a href="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/aceattorney/images/f/f9/SoJ_Objection%21.png/revision/latest?cb=20210615182206" class="image"><img alt="SoJ Objection!" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="260" height="183" data-image-name="SoJ Objection!.png" data-image-key="SoJ_Objection%21.png" data-relevant="1" data-src="https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/aceattorney/images/f/f9/SoJ_Objection%21.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/260?cb=20210615182206" class="lazyload" /></a>
</line><line>Apollo:
W-Wait a second! <textEffects>(What do I do...?!)</textEffects>
</line><line>Judge:
Does the defense wish to raise an objection?
</line><line>Apollo:
Err... Umm... <textEffects>(There's got to be some way to save Nahyuta!)</textEffects>
</line><line>Phoenix:
...Apollo. It all goes back to that incident twenty-three years ago. It's branded him the son of a criminal.
</line><line>Apollo:
So if we could once and for all prove that Dhurke didn't try to assassinate Amara...
</line><line>Phoenix:
Right. Nahyuta and Rayfa's father would no longer be viewed as a criminal.
</line><line>Apollo:
But I thought there wasn't any evidence left... ...because it was all destroyed in the fire. And Dhurke investigated the matter for years, but never managed to learn anything new.
</line><line>Phoenix:
.........Really? Nothing at all? Could an exceptional lawyer like Dhurke try that long and really uncover nothing at all? He had over two decades, Apollo.
</line><line>Apollo:
Huh? <textEffects>(He's right. I doubt Dhurke would've gone to his grave without discovering something new. He must've secretly planted something to topple Ga'ran with somewhere.)</textEffects>
</line><line>Phoenix:
Take another look at the evidence. You just might find what we need to break out of this situation with in there.
</line><line>Apollo:
G-Got it.
</line><line>Judge:
.........If the defense is done stalling for time, I shall now render my verdict.
</line><line>Apollo:
